Pat @duck breasts{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Place skin sides down in a #large pan{}. Cook over
medium heat until skin is crisp and most of the fat has rendered,
~{15-20%minutes}, pouring off fat as it renders.

> TIP: Lower heat if skin begins to brown too quickly.

Flip and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer
to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Peel, then dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce}
into ½-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover
by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until very tender,
~{15-20%minutes}. Drain.

Strip 1 tsp @thyme{1/4%ounce}(leaves stripped from stems) from stems; discard
stems. Mince @garlic{2%clove}. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce} and
@lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1} until you have ¼ cup.

> Use any remaining shallot as you like.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in pot used for potatoes over medium heat. Add
garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{20-30%seconds}. Add potatoes, ⅓ cup
@milk{6.75%ounce}, salt, and pepper. Mash until smooth and creamy with a
#potato masher{}. Add more milk a splash at a time if needed. Cover pot to
keep warm.

> TIP: If needed, add more milk a splash at a time.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for duck over medium
heat. Add minced shallot and thyme. Cook until shallot is softened,
~{2-3%minutes}. Add @chicken demi-glace{1}, @cranberry jam{2%tablespoon}, and ¼
cup water, stirring to break up jam. Let simmer until thick and glossy,
~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with pepper and more
lemon juice to taste.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @watercress{2%ounce}, tomatoes, a squeeze of
lemon juice, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}; toss to thoroughly
coat. Season with salt and pepper. Thinly slice duck crosswise. Divide
potatoes and duck between plates. Drizzle duck with sauce. Serve with salad
on the side.